Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1503
H.P. 987 House of Representatives, April 8, 2025
Reference to the Committee on Marine Resources suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative GOLEK of Harpswell.
Cosponsored by Senator MOORE of Washington and
Representatives: EATON of Deer Isle, FARRIN of Jefferson, HEPLER of Woolwich, RIELLY
of Westbrook, SIMMONS of Waldoboro, STROUT of Harrington, THORNE of Carmel.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §6866 is enacted to read:
3 §6866. Green crab only wholesale dealer license
4 1. Definition. For the purposes of this section, unless the context indicates otherwise,
5 "green crab" means the species Carcinus maenas.
6 2. License required. A person may not engage in the activities authorized under this
7 section without a current:
8 A. Green crab only wholesale dealer license established by this section; or
9 B. Wholesale seafood license pursuant to section 6851.
10 3. License activities. The holder of a green crab only wholesale dealer license may,
11 in wholesale trade, buy, sell, process, ship or transport green crabs purchased directly from
12 harvesters in this State. A holder of a green crab only wholesale dealer license when buying
13 directly from a harvester may buy only from a harvester who possesses a license or permit
14 to harvest green crabs required under this Part. The harvester shall make the applicable
15 marine resources license or permit available for inspection upon the green crab only
16 wholesale dealer license holder's request.
17 4. License fee. The fee for a green crab only wholesale dealer license is $50.
18 5. Violation. A person who engages in activities authorized under subsection 3
19 without a license specified in subsection 2 is subject to a penalty established by the
20 department. The department may revoke or suspend a green crab only wholesale dealer
21 license for violation of this section.
22 6. Sunset. This section is repealed January 1, 2031.
23 7. Review. Prior to the repeal of this section pursuant to subsection 6, the department
24 shall conduct a review of the effectiveness of the green crab only wholesale dealer license
25 and submit a report to the 134th Legislature in 2030. The report must include the
26 department's recommendations concerning possible continuation or modification of the
27 green crab only wholesale dealer license.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This bill establishes a green crab only wholesale dealer license that allows a license
3300 holder to, in wholesale trade, buy, sell, process, ship or transport green crabs purchased
3311 directly from harvesters in this State. Current law allows a person to engage in these
3322 activities under a wholesale seafood license, which has a minimum license fee of $192.75.
3333 The license fee for a green crab only wholesale dealer license is $50.
34 The bill provides that a person who engages in these activities without a proper license
35 is subject to a penalty established by the Department of Marine Resources, and the
36 department may suspend or revoke the license.
37 The bill includes a sunset provision, which repeals the legislation January 1, 2031. The
38 bill directs the department to conduct a review of the effectiveness of the green crab only
39 wholesale dealer license prior to the repeal date. The department is required to submit to
Page 1 - 132LR1091(01)
410 the 134th Legislature in 2030 a report of the review, including any recommendations to
421 continue or modify the license.
Page 2 - 132LR1091(01)
